                                    "description": "<br><strong>STATUS:</strong> A General Atomics MQ-20 drone successfully demonstrated robot-wingman concepts by executing tactical commands from an F-22 pilot during a recent test flight.\n\n<br><strong>INTEL:</strong> This demonstration, utilizing Autonodyne's Bashi pilot-vehicle interface, showcases advancements in autonomous systems for the Air Force's Collaborative Combat Aircraft (CCA) program, where General Atomics (YFQ-42 \"Dark Merlin\"), Anduril (YFQ-44 \"Fury\"), and Northrop Grumman (\"Project Talon\") are competing to develop AI-controlled uncrewed fighter wingmen, integrating technologies like RTX Collins software and the government's Autonomy Government Reference Architecture (A-GRA).",
