                                    "description": "February 24, 2026 \u2013 Washington, DC \u2013 The Commercial Space Federation (CSF) is proud to announce the release of a new paper titled \u201cPerfecting Public-Private Partnerships: The Future of Government Space Contracts\u201d. The report offers government buyers a playbook for maximizing outcomes on public-private partnerships. \u201cWe are pleased this Administration is embracing commercial partnerships for space\u2014something CSF has long endorsed. The value proposition is clear\u2014taxpayers are paying for results, not just effort,\u201d said CSF President Dave Cavossa. This report, authored by Rational Futures, is based on dozens of industry recommendations for how the government can be a smart buyer and manager of commercial space missions. It provides a primer on public-private partnerships and makes recommendations to improve PPP outcomes. This includes robust market assessments, signal clear demand, competition, and stable requirements. Successful program design and implementation require planning, coordination, and collaboration among stakeholders throughout the lifecycle. When executed effectively, both the government and industry benefit. About CSFThe Commercial Space Federation (CSF) is the leading trade association representing the commercial space industry. We serve as the industry\u2019s voice to policymakers in the U.S. government, international governments and organizations, the media, and the public, advocating for policies that support growth and innovation in the space economy. Sign in by entering the code we sent to , or clicking the magic link in the email.",
